physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Physical examination: well-appearing; cardiopulmonary examination was unremarkable.

Swollen, plethoric face; swollen arms; swollen but supple neck; moist mucous membranes; jugular venous distention; well-healed defibrillator pocket; dilated collateral veins on chest wall; normal pulmonary examination; regular cardiac rate and rhythm without murmurs, rubs, or gallops; soft and nontender abdomen; no leg edema.
